###############################################
### MEDICAL DOCUMENTS (CLOUDINARY) APIS
###############################################

### 1. Upload Medical Document (Multipart Form - use Postman)
# Note: This requires file upload - test in Postman
POST http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

# In Postman:
# - Select POST request
# - Go to Body -> form-data
# - Add key: file (type: File) -> select your PDF/image
# - Add key: patient_id (type: Text) -> value: 9897
# - Add key: uploaded_by (type: Text) -> value: 9097
# - Add key: document_type (type: Text) -> value: Lab Report
# - Add key: category (type: Text) -> value: lab_results
# - Add key: description (type: Text) -> value: Blood test results

### 2. Get All Medical Documents
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents?limit=20

### 3. Get Documents by Patient ID
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/patient/9897

### 4. Get Documents by Patient with Filters
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/patient/9897?document_type=Lab Report&category=lab_results

### 5. Get Documents by Uploader (Lab Reporter)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/uploaded-by/9097

### 6. Get Single Document by ID (replace with actual document ID)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/65f00000000000000000901

### 7. Get Document Statistics
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/stats/overview

### 8. Update Document Metadata (replace with actual document ID)
PUT http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/65f00000000000000000901
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Updated: Blood test results showing improvement",
  "document_type": "Blood Test",
  "category": "lab_results"
}

### 9. Delete Document (replace with actual document ID)
DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/65f00000000000000000901

### 10. Share Document with Doctor (replace with actual document ID)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/65f00000000000000000901/share
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "doctor_123",
  "permission": "view"
}

### 11. Get Document Access Logs (replace with actual document ID)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/medical-documents/65f00000000000000000901/access-logs

